<Theme width-navPanel-App="$space-28">
<App layout="vertical-sticky" var.recording="{false}" var.rightPaneSize="(measuring…)"
  onInit="subscribeRightPaneSize((s) => rightPaneSize = s.width + ' × ' + s.height)">
  <DataSource id="enhanceStatus" url="/__enhance/status" />
  <DataSource id="rpInfo" url="/__right-pane-info" />

  <ModalDialog id="urlInfoDialog" title="Right-pane info">
    <VStack gap="$space-3">
      <VStack gap="$space-1">
        <Text fontWeight="bold">URL</Text>
        <Text fontFamily="$fontFamily-monospace" fontSize="$fontSize-sm">{rpInfo.value && rpInfo.value.url}</Text>
        <HStack gap="$space-2">
          <Button
            label="Open in browser"
            size="sm"
            onClick="rpInfo.value &amp;&amp; openExternal(rpInfo.value.url)" />
        </HStack>
      </VStack>

      <VStack gap="$space-1" marginTop="$space-2">
        <Text fontWeight="bold">Screen size</Text>
        <Text fontFamily="$fontFamily-monospace" value="{rightPaneSize}" />
      </VStack>

      <VStack when="{rpInfo.value &amp;&amp; rpInfo.value.spawned}" gap="$space-1" marginTop="$space-2">
        <Text fontWeight="bold">Project server (.xmlui-desktop.json)</Text>
        <HStack gap="$space-2">
          <Text>command:</Text>
          <Text fontFamily="$fontFamily-monospace">{rpInfo.value.spawned.command}</Text>
        </HStack>
        <HStack gap="$space-2" when="{rpInfo.value.spawned.cwd}">
          <Text>cwd:</Text>
          <Text fontFamily="$fontFamily-monospace">{rpInfo.value.spawned.cwd}</Text>
        </HStack>
        <HStack gap="$space-2">
          <Text>port:</Text>
          <Text fontFamily="$fontFamily-monospace">{rpInfo.value.spawned.port}</Text>
        </HStack>
        <HStack gap="$space-2">
          <Text>path:</Text>
          <Text fontFamily="$fontFamily-monospace">{rpInfo.value.spawned.path}</Text>
        </HStack>
      </VStack>

      <VStack
        when="{rpInfo.value &amp;&amp; !rpInfo.value.spawned &amp;&amp; rpInfo.value.url === rpInfo.value.default_right_pane}"
        gap="$space-1"
        marginTop="$space-2">
        <Text fontSize="$fontSize-sm" color="$textColor-secondary">
          No .xmlui-desktop.json declared — using the internal loopback default.
        </Text>
      </VStack>
    </VStack>
  </ModalDialog>

  <AppHeader>
    <Theme paddingHorizontal-Button-sm="$space-1" fontSize-Button="$fontSize-md">
      <HStack gap="$space-0_5" verticalAlignment="center">
        <Theme fontSize-Button="$fontSize-lg">
          <Button
            label="ⓘ"
            variant="ghost"
            tooltip="Show right-pane info"
            onClick="rpInfo.refetch(); urlInfoDialog.open()" />
        </Theme>
        <Button
          label="A−"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Decrease app font size"
          onClick="window.setAppFontSize(window.getAppFontSize() - 1)" />
        <Button
          label="A+"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Increase app font size"
          onClick="window.setAppFontSize(window.getAppFontSize() + 1)" />
        <Button
          label="{recording ? '⏹ stop' : '🎤 voice'}"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Voice input — click to start, click again to send"
          onClick="recording ? (recording = false, voiceStop(t => { if (t) toTurn('voice: ' + t); })) : (voiceStart(), $pathname !== '/talk' && navigate('/talk'), recording = true)" />
        <Button
          label="📸"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Capture screenshot and send to claude"
          onClick="captureScreenshot()" />
        <Button
          label="1"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Permission menu: send keystroke 1"
          onClick="sendKeys('1\r')" />
        <Button
          label="2"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Permission menu: send keystroke 2"
          onClick="sendKeys('2\r')" />
        <Button
          label="3"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Permission menu: send keystroke 3"
          onClick="sendKeys('3\r')" />
        <Button
          label="Yes"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Send 'yes' as a user turn"
          onClick="toTurn('yes')" />
        <Button
          label="No"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Send 'no' as a user turn"
          onClick="toTurn('no')" />
        <Button
          label="Esc"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Send Esc to interrupt"
          onClick="(sendKeys('\x1b'), escSuppressed = true)" />
      </HStack>
    </Theme>
  </AppHeader>

  <NavPanel>
    <property name="logoTemplate">
      <Fragment/>
    </property>
    <NavLink label="Talk" to="/talk" />
    <NavLink label="Worklist" to="/" exact="true" />
    <NavLink label="Commits" to="/commits" />
    <NavLink label="Issues" to="/issues" />
    <NavLink label="Sessions" to="/sessions" />
    <NavLink label="Context" to="/context" />
    <NavLink label="README" to="/readme" />
  </NavPanel>

  <VStack
    when="{enhanceStatus.value && !enhanceStatus.value.enhanced}"
    padding="$space-4"
    gap="$space-3"
    backgroundColor="$color-info-50"
    borderBottom="1px solid $color-info-200">
    <Heading level="h3">Configure agent coordination</Heading>
    <Markdown content="The agent tools drawer hosts these views, all driven by data the agent produces or your interaction with it. The header at the top is pinned, so font-size controls (`A−` / `A+`), the 🎤 voice toggle, menu keystrokes (`1` / `2` for the agent's permission prompts), conversational replies (`Yes` / `No`), and `Esc` (interrupt) all stay reachable from any tab.

- **Talk** — live transcript of the current session, with alternating user / assistant turns and a spinner that shows while you wait for a reply. Click 🎤 voice in the AppHeader to dictate from any tab; clicking it again sends the transcript as a fresh user turn. Pasted screenshots render inline as clickable thumbnails (click for fullscreen).
- **Worklist** — renders `resources/worklist.json` as a checklist of pending items the agent has proposed. You triage with checkboxes; *Talk to agent*, *Approve selected*, and *Drop selected* round-trip the result back to the agent as a fresh user turn (via the `toTurn` shell helper). Optional feedback typed in the box rides along with the action.
- **Commits** — recent commits, with one-click push to origin when you are ahead.
- **Issues** — list of open / closed GitHub issues for the current repo (via the local `gh` CLI), with a one-click button to open the New-issue page on github.com. Click an issue to expand its body inline; pasted screenshots render as clickable thumbnails.
- **Sessions** — browse and search past agent sessions for this project. Claude Code and Codex histories are auto-detected from local transcripts.
- **Context** — see what Claude Code is loading for this project (CLAUDE.md + one-hop @-imports, the per-project memory tree, hooks, settings) with substring search across all four and grep -C style hit snippets. Cross-references inside memory files (e.g. MEMORY.md's `[foo.md](memory/foo.md)`) navigate inline.
- **README** — this project's README rendered for quick reference.

Setting up writes:
- `.claude/xmlui-desktop-conventions.md` — the conventions sidecar (worklist schema and lifecycle, helper APIs, charting via `EChart`, what belongs in the right pane).
- An `@`-import line in `CLAUDE.md` (created if missing, appended idempotently if present) so every new Claude Code session in this project pulls those conventions in automatically.

What setup deliberately does **not** do:

- Create `resources/worklist.json`. The Worklist tab works without it — when the file is missing, the route serves an empty default and the worklist shows *(none)*. The agent writes to the file the first time it proposes items.
- Inject `&lt;script src=&quot;/__shell/helpers.js&quot;&gt;` into your `index.html`. That script is only needed if your own xmlui markup wants to call `toShell`/`toTurn`/`openExternal`/`logToHost` (e.g., a custom Approve button you wire). The drawer's tabs work either way." />
    <Text fontSize="$fontSize-sm" color="$textColor-secondary">
      Existing Claude Code sessions in this project need /clear or restart
      to pick up the new CLAUDE.md.
    </Text>
    <HStack>
      <Button
        label="Set up"
        onClick="window.fetch('/__enhance/run').then(() => enhanceStatus.refetch())" />
    </HStack>
  </VStack>

  <Pages fallbackPath="/">
    <Page url="/"><Workspace /></Page>
    <Page url="/talk"><Talk /></Page>
    <Page url="/sessions"><Sessions /></Page>
    <Page url="/context"><Context /></Page>
    <Page url="/issues"><Issues /></Page>
    <Page url="/commits"><Commits /></Page>
    <Page url="/readme"><Readme /></Page>
  </Pages>
</App>
</Theme>
